          <updateDate>2015-04-29T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Space Leadership Preservation Act of 2015</b></p> <p> Establishes a 10-year term of office for the Administrator of the National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA). </p> <p>Establishes a NASA Board of Directors together with appointment criteria.</p> <p>Requires the President to appoint the Administrator from among a list of nominees provided by the Board, and a Deputy Administrator from among a separate list of Board nominees. </p> <p>Authorizes the Board to establish special commissions as it deems necessary.</p> <p>Requires the Board to provide: (1) NASA's proposed annual budget; (2) annual reports on spaceflight infrastructure, unique space capabilities, and the availability of qualified U.S. workers necessary to maintain such infrastructure and capabilities; (3) reports on specific policy matters; and (4) once every four years a review of current space programs and a vision for future space exploration. </p> <p>Authorizes NASA to enter into contracts for rocket propulsion systems and manned and unmanned space transportation vehicles and payloads. </p>]]></text>
